from pyspark.sql.types import StructType, StructField, StringType, IntegerType

	{'id': 2, 'desc': u'STATE ENTERPRISE EMPLOYEE'},
	{'id': 3, 'desc': u'EMPLOYEE'},
	{'id': 4, 'desc': u'OWN BUSINESS'},
	{'id': 5, 'desc': u'HOUSE WIFE'},
	{'id': 6, 'desc': u'STUDENT'},
	{'id': 7, 'desc': u'FREELANCE'},
	{'id': 8, 'desc': u'AGRICULTURAL'},
	{'id': 9, 'desc': u'WORKER'},
	{'id':10, 'desc': u'PRIEST'},
	{'id':11, 'desc': u'RETIRE'},
	{'id':12, 'desc': u'OTHER (WORK)'},
	{'id':13, 'desc': u'OTHER (FREELANCE)'},
]
schema = StructType([
    StructField("id", IntegerType(), True),
    StructField("desc", StringType(), True),
])

]

%pyspark
df_demog =spark.read.csv(
    		path="data/demographic.csv",
    		header=True,
    		inferSchema=True, 
    		timestampFormat= "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss",
    		mode="DROPMALFORMED",
	    )
#z.show(df_demog)
df_demog.show()

%pyspark
from pyspark.sql.types import IntegerType
from pyspark.sql.functions import lit,regexp_replace
df_demographic=df_demog\
    .join(df_occupation, df_demog.ocp_cd==df_occupation.id)\
    .withColumnRenamed('desc', 'occupation')\
    .drop('ocp_cd')\
    .drop('id')\
    .join(df_marriage_status, df_demog.mar_st_cd==df_marriage_status.id)\
    .withColumnRenamed('desc', 'marriage_status')\
    .drop('mar_st_cd')\
    .drop('id')\
    .join(df_gender, df_demog.gnd_cd==df_gender.id)\
    .withColumnRenamed('desc', 'gender')\
    .drop('gnd_cd')\
    .drop('id')\
    .join(df_income_segment, df_demog.idv_incm_seg_cd==df_income_segment.id)\
    .withColumnRenamed('desc', 'income_segment')\
    .drop('idv_incm_seg_cd')\
    .drop('id')\
    .join(df_family_income_segment, df_demog.fam_incm_seg_cd==df_family_income_segment.id)\
    .withColumnRenamed('desc', 'family_income_segment')\
    .drop('fam_incm_seg_cd')\
    .drop('id')\
    .withColumnRenamed('act_strt_dt', 'account_start_date')\
    .withColumnRenamed('brth_estb_yr', 'age')\
    .join(df_education_level, df_demog.ed_lvl_cd==df_education_level.id)\
    .withColumnRenamed('desc', 'education_level')\
    .drop('ed_lvl_cd')\
    .drop('id')
    
df_demographic=df_demographic.withColumn("age", lit(2018)-df_demographic["age"].cast(IntegerType()))
#z.show(df_demographic)

%pyspark
df=df_cctran\
    .join(df_ccinf, df_cctran.card_no_encpt==df_ccinf.card_no_encpt)\
    .drop('card_no_encpt')\
    .drop('card_org_no')\
    .withColumnRenamed('eff_dt', 'transaction_date')\
    .withColumnRenamed('txn_amt', 'transaction_amount')\
    .withColumnRenamed('bill_cyc', 'billing_cycle')\
    .withColumnRenamed('opn_dt', 'cc_open date')\
    .withColumnRenamed('cr_lmt_amt', 'credit_limit_amount')\
    .withColumnRenamed('past_due_amt', 'past_due_amount')\
    .join(df_mcc, df_mcc.mcc_no==df_cctran.mcc)\
    .withColumnRenamed('category', 'mcc_category')\
    .withColumnRenamed('group', 'mcc_group')\
    .drop('mcc')\
    .drop('mcc_no')
df=df\
    .join(df_cc_map, df_cc_map.cc_cst_no==df.main_cc_cst_no)\
    .drop('main_cc_cst_no')\
    .drop('cc_cst_no')
df=df\
    .join(df_demographic, df_demographic.u_id==df.u_id)\
    .drop('u_id')
df1=df
z.show(df1)

    .groupby(
        #'prim_seg_cd','prim_sub_seg_cd','occupation', 'marriage_status', 'gender', 'income_segment', 'family_income_segment', 'education_level',\
        'age','mcc_category',\
        #year('transaction_date').alias("tx_year"),
        #dayofyear('transaction_date').alias('tx_dayofy'),\

    .agg({'transaction_amount':'sum', 'credit_limit_amount':'avg', 'past_due_amount':'sum'})\
    #.filter("avg(past_due_amount)<1500 and avg(credit_limit_amount) < 300000 and avg(transaction_amount)<20000")\
    .filter("sum(past_due_amount)<100000 and 1<sum(past_due_amount)")\
    .orderBy('mcc_category')
)

paragraphs.title: Age-Credit Limit-Transaction Amount
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
from pyspark.sql.functions import year, mean, month, dayofmonth, dayofyear, hour, minute, weekofyear
from pyspark.sql.functions import lit
from pyspark.sql import functions as F
z.show(df1\
    .groupby(
        #'prim_seg_cd','prim_sub_seg_cd','occupation', 'marriage_status', 'gender', 'income_segment', 'family_income_segment', 'education_level',\
        'age','mcc_category',\
        #year('transaction_date').alias("tx_year"),
        #dayofyear('transaction_date').alias('tx_dayofy'),\
    )\
    .agg({'transaction_amount':'sum', 'credit_limit_amount':'avg', 'past_due_amount':'sum'})\
    #.filter("avg(past_due_amount)<1500 and avg(credit_limit_amount) < 300000 and avg(transaction_amount)<20000")\
    .filter("sum(transaction_amount)>500000")\
    .orderBy('mcc_category')
)

paragraphs.title: Age-Mcc Profiling
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
from pyspark.sql.functions import year, mean, month, dayofmonth, dayofyear, hour, minute, weekofyear
from pyspark.sql.functions import lit
from pyspark.sql import functions as F
z.show(df1\
    .groupby(
        #'prim_seg_cd','prim_sub_seg_cd','occupation', 'marriage_status', 'gender', 'income_segment', 'family_income_segment', 'education_level',\
        'age','gender','mcc_category',\
        #year('transaction_date').alias("tx_year"),
        #dayofyear('transaction_date').alias('tx_dayofy'),\
    )\
    .agg({'transaction_amount':'avg', 'credit_limit_amount':'avg', 'past_due_amount':'sum'})\
    #.filter("avg(past_due_amount)<1500 and avg(credit_limit_amount) < 300000 and avg(transaction_amount)<20000")\
    .filter("sum(transaction_amount)>500000")\
    .orderBy('mcc_category')
)
